{{afc comment|1=trimming these off. the parameter works as "burial" so no need to use "burial"[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 03:35, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=added parameters Interred_individual and Mausoleum is planned to be added but I messed up in template editing[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:40, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=now we have a 'burial' and 'burial goods' parameter. So a lot of these pages might not be marked on our wiki as having unknown parameters. But specifically keeping this comment here in case of import, these parameters should be added to [[Template:infobox ancient site]] rather than deleted from this draft or article[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:01, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=I hope this is not too annoying but this article is gonna be placed under [[:Category:Pages using infobox ancient site with unknown parameters]] and there is a decent chance these unknown parameters are ones I want added to the main template like burial chamber structure and burial goods. Please do not use any bots that just remove the unknown parameters without looking at them. This was added through [[Special:MassEditRegex]] to all pages with the category so apologies if it was just some kind of an error like the image parameter being in Japanese[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 06:00, 27 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{Infobox ancient site|type = [[Zenpokoenfun]] |name =丸隈山古墳 |image ={{image募集中|cat=福岡市}} |imageキャプション = |別名 = | part_of = {{ill|Imajuku Kofun Cluster|ja|今宿古墳群}} |location ={{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}} {{ill|Fukuoka City|ja|福岡市}} {{ill|Nishi-ku, Fukuoka|ja|西区}} {{ill|Susenji, Fukuoka|ja|周船寺}} |coordinates = |緯度度 =33 |緯度分 =34 |緯度秒 =25.3 |経度度 =130 |経度分 =15 |経度秒 =7.1 |omitted =JP-40 |type ={{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}} |area =Total length 84.6 m, rear circular section diameter 60 m, front section 25 m |埋葬施設 = |burial goods =Bronze mirrors, swords, iron arrowheads, etc. |陪塚 = |築造時期 =Early 5th century |被葬者 = |陵墓 = |史跡 =Designated as a [[National Historic Site of Japan]] |有形文化財 = |埋蔵文化財包蔵地番号 = |特記事項 = |地図 =Japan Fukuoka |地図2 = |アイコン = |ラベル = |ラベルcoordinates = }} '''Marukumayama Kofun''' (丸隈山古墳) is a {{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}} located at the foot of {{ill|Takasu Mountain|ja|高祖山}} in {{ill|Susenji, Fukuoka|ja|周船寺}}, {{ill|Nishi-ku, Fukuoka|ja|西区}}, {{ill|Fukuoka City|ja|福岡市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}. It is Historic Site1 as one of the key tumuli in the {{ill|Imajuku Kofun Cluster|ja|今宿古墳群}}, which has been recognized as a [[National Historic Site of Japan]].
== map_size and Features == The tumulus measures 84.6 meters in total length, with the rear circular section having a diameter of 60 meters and the front section measuring 25 meters. It is estimated to be the burial site of a chieftain from the early 5th century.
The kofun features a {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber}} made of basalt and an internal stone sarcophagus, which are open to public viewing at no cost. It is one of the few nationally Historic Site1 tumuli where visitors can directly see the stone sarcophagus. According to the Edo period document {{ill|Chikuzen Koku Zoku Fudoki|ja|筑前国続風土記}} by {{ill|Kaibara Ekken|ja|貝原益軒}}, burial goods such as bronze mirrors, swords, and iron arrowheads were excavated from the site.
Other finds include tomoe-shaped bronze implements, swords, magatama beads, and tubular beads. The human remains discovered in the tomb are believed to belong to a male.== See Also == * {{ill|Yamanohane No. 1 Kofun|ja|山ノ鼻1号墳}}
== External Links == * {{Historic SiteDatabase|401|2614|Imajuku Kofun Cluster}} * [https://bunkazai.city.fukuoka.lg.jp/cultural_properties/detail/item_id:101009 Imajuku Kofun Cluster (Marukumayama Kofun)] - Fukuoka City Historic Site * [https://www.city.fukuoka.lg.jp/nishiku/c-shinko/charm/nisikunotakara/marukumayama_kofun.html Marukumayama Kofun] - Fukuoka City Homepage
